House Resolution 478
By: Representatives Carson of the 46th and Cooper of the 45th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Reverend Art Wilder upon the occasion of his retirement; and
2 for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Reverend Art Wilder has long demonstrated an unwavering commitment to
4 teaching the Gospel, witnessing Christ through word and deed, and addressing the physical,
5 psychological, intellectual, and spiritual needs of others; and
6 WHEREAS, he has devoted four decades to answering God's call, serving in ministry with
7 faithfulness and dedication, including 38 years as the minister over pastoral care at Johnson
8 Ferry Baptist Church; and
9 WHEREAS, throughout his tenure at Johnson Ferry Baptist Church, Reverend Wilder served
10 in numerous capacities, including as pastor over discipleship, missions, singles, and senior
11 adults; and
12 WHEREAS, his background in engineering helped him develop effective systems and equip
13 others to provide compassionate spiritual care, ensuring that the church remained personally
14 connected with its members, especially during times of illness, crisis, and loss; and
