15 WHEREAS, Reverend Wilder's wisdom and kindness have been a source of comfort and
16 guidance for countless individuals over the years, offering strength, encouragement, and care
17 to those in need; and
18 WHEREAS, he has touched the lives of many through his steadfast leadership, his ability to
19 uplift and inspire others in their faith, and his unwavering commitment to the ministry of
20 Christ; and
21 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper to recognize the outstanding accomplishments
22 of this devoted and pious man as he retires from full-time ministry, leaving a lasting legacy
23 of faith, service, and love.
24 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
25 the members of this body recognize and commend Reverend Art Wilder upon the grand
26 occasion of his retirement, express gratitude for his 40 years of ministry, and extend best
27 wishes for future health and happiness.
28 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
29 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
30 Reverend Art Wilder.
